meanings.definition: To fulfill or carry out (a task or obligation) to a greater extent than required or expected.
meanings.sent1: She always tries to overfulfill her duties at work.
meanings.sent2: The team managed to overfulfill their sales target for the month.
meanings.sent3: It's like she's on a mission to overfulfill every assignment she gets.
meanings.sent4: His dedication to overfulfilling his promises is truly admirable.
meanings.sent5: The student's effort to overfulfill the project requirements paid off with an A+ grade.

meanings.definition: To exceed or surpass (a goal or target) in terms of completion or achievement.
meanings.sent1: The company was able to overfulfill its production quota for the year.
meanings.sent2: They managed to overfulfill their fundraising goal for the charity event.
meanings.sent3: It almost feels like a competition to see who can overfulfill the set objectives.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to overfulfill expectations propelled her to success.
meanings.sent5: The athlete's training regimen allowed him to overfulfill his personal best record.
